    "e, State reconstruction and state-preparation-and-measurement (SPAM) error analysis using repeated PSB readout at B 0 = 0.79 T and T = 1 K in (5, 3).",
    "We initialize s 0 = |↓↓⟩ using the algorithmic initialization or |↑↓⟩ by π-pulsing on Q1 after the algorithmic |↓↓⟩ initialization.",
    "We then perform n PSB readouts, through which the state evolves into s n.",
    "Finally, we apply machine learning (ML) on the readout outcomes m 1 -m n to extract the initialization, readout and spin-flip probabilities and reconstruct the states.",
    "The results are shown in the table and the plots."
